JSE-listed Long4Life has appointed Kevin Hedderwick COO and executive director, effective immediately. Hedderwick, who was previously CEO of Famous Brands, joins several other business stalwarts at Brian Joffe&rsquo;s newly established and recently listed lifestyle investment company. In April, Long4Life CEO and founder Joffe listed his latest venture on the main board of the Johannesburg bourse, appointing Peter Riskowitz as CFO and executive director effective May 1. Long4Life&rsquo;s chairperson is Graham Dempster, while other independent nonexecutive directors include Tasneem Abdool-Samad, Lionel Jacobs and Colin Datnow, with Jason Joffe as alternate director.